  <prompt>
    Create `ComposeEmptyState.tsx` — the default-open state shown when Compose is mounted without a document context. Per the locked R1 decision (CLAUDE.md), this state surfaces two affordances: "Browse / open file" (Path B — upload, ephemeral) and "Search for Document" (Path A — pick an existing `sprk_document` record). Both affordances dispatch PaneEventBus events; receivers are stubbed in R1 per FR-20.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React/TypeScript developer fluent in Fluent UI v9 empty-state patterns and the SpaarkeAi PaneEventBus contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `ComposeEmptyState.tsx` renders a centered Fluent v9 empty-state UI with Browse + Search buttons, both wired to PaneEventBus dispatch (using contracts from Task 041). Build green; ui-test green; dark mode renders.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-18 mandates the two-option empty state. The decision is locked in CLAUDE.md (Decisions Made — "R1 default-open: Empty state with Browse + Search options"). This state is the first thing a user sees when opening Compose without coming from a Path A modal launch.
    </background>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 dark mode via semantic tokens; centered layout uses `makeStyles` not inline styles.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No direct auth handling — defer to `@spaarke/auth` if either action requires elevated scope.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">REUSE existing modal/picker patterns from SemanticSearch + ConversationPane; NO custom Browse/Search abstraction.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No custom DOCX-feature integration outside TipTap OOB.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <justification>
    <existing>Fluent v9 `EmptyState` / `Card` primitives exist; no Spaarke empty-state component is reused for Compose because Browse + Search are Compose-specific affordances.</existing>
    <extension>No — empty-state UIs are typically per-surface. The two affordances (Browse upload, Search picker) are unique to Compose's two entry paths (A and B).</extension>
    <cost-of-doing-nothing>FR-18 fails — users opening Compose with no document context see a blank pane; Path B (ephemeral upload) has no UI entry point; the Path A search picker is not surfaced.</cost-of-doing-nothing>
  </justification>

