  <notes>
    Completed 2026-06-29 by Wave 4 autonomous sub-agent.

    Outputs:
      - `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/compose/ComposeEmptyState.tsx` (NEW, 240 LOC)
      - `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/compose/index.ts` (NEW barrel)

    CTAs implemented:
      - "Browse / open file" — `appearance="primary"` + `DocumentArrowUpRegular` icon → `onBrowseRequested` callback prop
      - "Search for Document" — `appearance="outline"` + `SearchRegular` icon → `onSearchRequested` callback prop
      - Optional `disabled?: boolean` prop renders both as focusable-but-inactionable while parent bootstraps

    Design pivot (Path C — pivot to comply with cleaner constraint):
      POML §steps[2,3] phrased the CTAs as "dispatches `compose:browse-requested` /
      `compose:search-requested` PaneEventBus events"; dispatch instructions stated
      "stateless presentation component — receives callbacks via props for the two
      actions". Resolved by Path C — callback-prop design honours both readings:
      the COMPONENT is pure presentation; the PARENT (ComposeWorkspace, task 042)
      wires the callbacks to PaneEventBus dispatch with whatever event shape it
      chooses. Avoids inventing new discriminants on `WorkspacePaneEvent` (which is
      a closed string-literal union; additive discriminants would require editing
      `@spaarke/ai-widgets/events/PaneEventTypes.ts` — out of scope for task 044
      and not in Task 041 contracts). No ADR tensions surfaced.

    Component justification (CLAUDE.md §11):
      - Existing: 3 EmptyState components inspected (DailyBriefing, SemanticSearch,
        LegalWorkspace ActivityFeed/NotificationPanel). All are surface-specific
        message displays; none has a two-CTA card layout.
      - Extension: cannot extend — they encode their own message semantics +
        iconography; a generic two-CTA primitive would need to be hoisted to
        `@spaarke/ui-components` first (separate work, not Phase 4 scope).
      - Cost-of-doing-nothing: FR-18 fails (blank pane on default-open; locked R1
        decisions design.md §14 row 5 — Browse + Search — unreachable).

    Build verification:
      - `npm run typecheck` (SpaarkeAi): 0 surface-owned errors (78 pre-existing
        shared-lib errors deferred per Phase B tsc-surface-gate, baseline unchanged).
      - `npm run build` (SpaarkeAi Vite): ✅ 3576 modules transformed / 0 errors /
        13.55s; bundle includes ComposeEmptyState.tsx.
      - `Build-AllClientComponents.ps1`: ❌ FAILS on `Spaarke.Compose.Components`
        (`src/utils/docxBridge.ts` TS2352 error). UNRELATED to task 044 — that
        package belongs to sibling task 045 (TipTap+DOCX bridge) which is in
        parallel-flight on the same wave. Task 044 has zero imports from
        `@spaarke/compose-components` (verified via grep). My deliverable lives
        in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/`, not in the failing package.

    Tests added: none in task 044 itself. The component is pure presentation +
    callbacks; the testing obligation is satisfied by the existing jest setup +
    the smoke test deferred to Phase 6 (task 060/061). KEEP category: would be
    "presentational component" per ADR-038 §7 — small-N integration tests
    preferred over isolated unit tests for pure render+click components.

    ADR conformance:
      - ADR-021 Fluent v9 + dark mode: ✅ semantic tokens only (`tokens.colorNeutralBackground1`,
        `tokens.colorNeutralForeground1`, `tokens.spacingHorizontalM` etc.); no hex; no rgba;
        no `colorBrand*` hardcodes. Dark mode adapts automatically via Fluent.
      - ADR-022 React 19: ✅ `React.JSX.Element` return; functional component; no class refs.
      - ADR-028 Auth: ✅ no auth surface in component (correct — empty state has no privileged
        ops; receivers in parent route to `@spaarke/auth` if needed).
      - ADR-030 Typed event channels: ✅ no inline event dispatch; parent owns event shape;
        no new discriminants added to `WorkspacePaneEvent` (preserves existing union surface).
      - ADR-015 Tier 3: ✅ no user-content fields in component or props.

    Accessibility:
      - `role="region"` + `aria-label="Compose — no document open"` on outer container
      - `role="group"` + `aria-label="Open document options"` on CTA row
      - Each `<Button>` carries explicit `aria-label` echoing intent
      - Both buttons keyboard-reachable (native Fluent v9 buttons; Tab + Enter/Space work)
      - Focus rings come from Fluent tokens (dark-mode safe)
      - `data-testid` hooks for E2E: `compose-empty-state`, `compose-empty-state-browse`,
        `compose-empty-state-search`

    Open items for downstream tasks:
      - Task 042 (ComposeWorkspace): will import `ComposeEmptyState` from
        `@/components/compose`; will provide `onBrowseRequested` + `onSearchRequested`
        callbacks wired to PaneEventBus dispatch (or direct SPE picker / SemanticSearch
        invocation per workspace orchestration design).
      - Task 045 (ComposeEditor): unrelated — TipTap bridge work in
        `@spaarke/compose-components`.
      - Sibling task 043 (ComposeToolbar): independently created
        `ComposeToolbar.tsx` in the same directory; my barrel only re-exports
        ComposeEmptyState. Task 043 (or task 042 orchestration) should append
        the ComposeToolbar export to the barrel when its API is finalised.
      - DEFERRED (future): if the two-CTA card layout becomes useful elsewhere,
        consider hoisting an `<EmptyStateCard>` primitive to `@spaarke/ui-components`.
        Not in this project's scope per §11 (no second consumer surfaced).
  </notes>
